{"batch":"abstraction_fitness","batch_index":3,"assessments":{"abstraction_fitness":72.0},"dimension_notes":{"abstraction_fitness":{"evidence":["`nba_pbp_utils.py` combines unrelated concerns in one project-wide helper surface: HTTP fetching (`fetch_playbyplay_payload`, lines 54-64), dataframe normalization (`actions_to_dataframe`, lines 67-80), possession grouping (`build_valid_possessions`, lines 104-111), foul counting (`count_defensive_fouls`, lines 114-122), score-side inference (`infer_team_score_side`, lines 125-153), and CLI-style output formatting (`format_output_preview`, lines 168-183). Most production scripts import directly from this single module instead of from bounded domain modules.","The seed scripts are thin orchestration layers over that generic helper module rather than consumers of a domain API. `build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` pulls eight names from `nba_pbp_utils` (lines 5-15) and then reconstructs possession-table logic inline in `build_table` (lines 20-84). `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py` does the same with nine imported names (lines 5-16) and its own possession/event assembly (lines 21-104).","The same possession-to-foul pipeline is re-derived in multiple places instead of being named once and reused through an explicit domain abstraction: `build_table` groups `valid` by `possession_group` and computes foul flags in `build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` lines 27-59; `build_possession_table_for_game` repeats the same pattern in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` lines 57-73; `build_foul_vector` repeats it again in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` lines 106-130; `parse_possessions` repeats related grouping and defensive-foul extraction in `step2_build_possessions.py` lines 33-65.","There is little classic indirection overhead: no delegation-heavy classes, no one-implementation base classes, and no parameter-bag APIs showed up in the production files reviewed. The main abstraction weakness is low definition directness at the module boundary, not wrapper chains or type-erasing interfaces."] ,"impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high","sub_axes":{"abstraction_leverage":68.0,"indirection_cost":83.0,"interface_honesty":82.0,"delegation_density":96.0,"definition_directness":52.0,"type_discipline":89.0}}},"issues":[{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"generic_helper_sink","summary":"`nba_pbp_utils.py` has become a catch-all helper module instead of a bounded domain API.","related_files":["nba_pbp_utils.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","step2_build_possessions.py"],"evidence":["`nba_pbp_utils.py` mixes transport (`fetch_playbyplay_payload`, lines 54-64), parsing (`actions_to_dataframe`, lines 67-80), domain derivation (`build_valid_possessions`, lines 104-111; `count_defensive_fouls`, lines 114-122; `infer_team_score_side`, lines 125-153), constants, and presentation (`format_output_preview`, lines 168-183) in one module.","Every main production script imports several unrelated names from that same module, for example `build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` lines 5-15 and `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py` lines 5-16, which makes the helper module the de facto project API rather than a set of explicit domain packages."],"suggestion":"Split `nba_pbp_utils.py` into bounded modules such as `pbp_fetch.py`, `pbp_frames.py`, `possession_model.py`, and `reporting.py`, then have scripts import a small number of explicit domain functions like `build_possession_table(...)` or `extract_defensive_foul_events(...)` instead of assembling workflows from generic helpers.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"missing_domain_boundaries"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"rederived_possession_pipeline","summary":"Possession-to-foul logic is reimplemented across scripts instead of being captured once behind a direct domain abstraction.","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","step2_build_possessions.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` lines 27-59 groups possessions and computes defensive foul counts to build table rows.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` lines 57-73 repeats the same grouping and foul-flag construction for season aggregation.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` lines 106-130 again rebuilds the same flow as `build_foul_vector`, while `step2_build_possessions.py` lines 33-65 performs a closely related possession walk with its own derived outputs.","Because the core workflow lives as copy-and-adjust logic in scripts, developers have to know several helper functions and reconstruct the same concept repeatedly rather than call one well-named domain function."],"suggestion":"Extract one shared domain-level function that returns a possession-level representation from play-by-play data, then layer specialized outputs on top of that shared result instead of rebuilding grouping and foul classification in each script.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"missing_domain_boundaries"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The project grew around script entrypoints first, so shared behavior accumulated in a generic utility module instead of a small set of domain modules.","Common basketball-domain concepts like 'possession table' and 'defensive foul vector' were not promoted into first-class APIs, so each script reconstructs them locally."],"likely_symptoms":["generic_helper_sink","rederived_possession_pipeline"],"possible_false_positives":["The packet's facade-module signal on the seed files appears tool-driven by heavy imports; the real issue is not re-exporting but that these scripts depend on a broad helper surface."]}}
